<paragraph id="455F36E84A64E015FF0CFA89FE6FFAC1" blockId="8.[151,463,1264,1327]" box="[151,463,1300,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FF0CFA89FF59FAC1" box="[151,249,1301,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,169,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[159,1428,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 1 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs.1 A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FE9FFA89FE8FFAC1" box="[260,303,1301,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[188,1409,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[164,1423,166,1884]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species, lateral view. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366552/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">4 A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FEA1FA89FEC4FAC1" box="[314,356,1301,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[175,1425,310,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1435,264,1750]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–P. Faces of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., Male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female. P. Glaberana purva sp. nov., male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366558/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">7 A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FEF4FA88FE2BFAC1" box="[367,395,1300,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 15" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,166,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1425,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 15 A–H. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366574/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">15</figureCitation>
A–H.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="455F36E84A64E015FF0CFAC1FB55FA75" blockId="8.[151,1437,1373,1867]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A64E015FF0CFAC1FF71FA99" box="[151,209,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectingRegion id="8724F80A4A64E015FF0CFAC1FF71FA99" box="[151,209,1373,1399]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
. Head ochraceous, ocelli black; eyes brown; pronotum and mesonotum black with posterior margin paler; forewings ochraceous; thoracic sternites and pleurites largely black with broad ochraceous margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="455F36E84A64E015FF5CFA39FB29F9A1" blockId="8.[151,1437,1373,1867]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A64E015FF5CFA39FED5FA51" box="[199,373,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectingRegion id="8724F80A4A64E015FF5CFA39FEA1FA51" box="[199,257,1445,1471]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male</collectingRegion>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer with digitate caudoventral process, without caudodorsal process, small lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FEFBFA55FE72FA0D" box="[352,466,1480,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 15" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,166,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1425,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 15 A–H. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366574/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 15 H</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate of uniform width, slightly broader medially and basally, with short setae (15 E). Style short, broad basally (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FDC7FA71FD67F9E9" box="[604,711,1516,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 15" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,166,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1425,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 15 A–H. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366574/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 15 F</figureCitation>
). Connective as long as wide at base (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FBEDFA71FB47F9E9" box="[1142,1255,1516,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 15" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,166,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1425,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 15 A–H. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366574/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 15 G</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus narrowed at apical half in lateral view, with two subapical, glabrous spine-like processes, distal process 
<date id="315E10284A64E015FB60F98DFAB7F9C5" box="[1275,1303,1553,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">2x</date>
longer than the proximal process, gonopore arising distad of base of proximal process (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A64E015FC7AF9A9FB9CF9A1" box="[993,1084,1588,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 15" captionStartId="50.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,166,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1425,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURES 15 A–H. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366574/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
A–D).
</paragraph>
